WEBVTT

00:10.788 --> 00:13.260
Previously on
The Last Man...

00:13.293 --> 00:15.464
We've got eyes on Agent Burgin.
Holed up in a church.

00:15.497 --> 00:17.602
‐Nowhere, Pennsylvania.
‐I have a visual.

00:17.636 --> 00:19.661
Permission to engage?

00:19.695 --> 00:22.567
Can you believe
Jennifer Brown is president?

00:22.601 --> 00:24.705
She's invincible.

00:24.738 --> 00:26.107
What if she's not?

00:26.140 --> 00:28.679
You know, right?
That you sleepwalk.

00:28.713 --> 00:29.815
You were up in the loft
last night.

00:29.848 --> 00:31.117
You could have broken your neck.

00:31.150 --> 00:33.421
They're after her. Not us.

00:33.455 --> 00:35.693
I just betrayed her because
you convinced me.

00:35.727 --> 00:37.062
No, "convinced" is strong.

00:44.878 --> 00:47.016
‐Did she see you?
‐No. No.

00:47.049 --> 00:48.553
No, she didn't see me.

00:48.586 --> 00:50.455
I'm not gonna tell you
how to run your fucking lab.

00:50.489 --> 00:52.727
Until we get to San Francisco,
this is my show.

01:23.656 --> 01:24.925
‐What?

01:24.958 --> 01:27.631
Ah... You think we should‐‐

01:27.664 --> 01:29.835
I don't know‐‐
make some sort of gesture,

01:29.868 --> 01:31.572
like an olive branch?

01:31.605 --> 01:34.176
Like what? Flowers?

01:34.210 --> 01:37.517
Just say we're sorry, maybe?

01:37.550 --> 01:39.688
I'm not sorry.

01:39.721 --> 01:42.192
‐Yeah, of course you're not.

01:42.226 --> 01:44.163
Hey, buddy.

01:45.700 --> 01:47.971
She lied to us,
almost got us killed.

01:49.608 --> 01:50.877
‐Got some extra fuel.
‐Yeah, I saw that.

01:50.910 --> 01:52.479
That's, um, that was smart.

01:54.685 --> 01:56.622
Good thinking.

01:56.655 --> 01:59.460
Empty the camper.
You two can ride in back.

02:01.665 --> 02:03.234
Yup. I think that did it.

02:03.268 --> 02:04.871
I don't think
she's angry anymore.

02:29.120 --> 02:30.857
Yeah, they know
it's a performance,

02:30.890 --> 02:32.994
so even if it's real,
they can't buy in though

02:33.028 --> 02:35.065
‐unless the stakes
are relatable.
‐Like what?

02:35.098 --> 02:36.769
‐Like buried alive?
‐Uh‐huh?

02:36.802 --> 02:39.006
Only really works if there's
something else in the box.

02:39.040 --> 02:41.144
‐Yeah, like what?
‐Like, uh, I don't know,

02:41.177 --> 02:42.747
a scorpion.
Or, like, a big‐ass spider.

02:42.781 --> 02:45.085
Life and death, it's too
theoretical, and besides,

02:45.118 --> 02:47.256
people don't think you're gonna
risk death for a magic show.

02:47.289 --> 02:49.761
They don't know
what an idiot you are.

02:49.795 --> 02:51.899
But if the trick
goes wrong‐‐ hey.

02:51.932 --> 02:54.938
But if the trick goes wrong

02:54.971 --> 02:56.842
and all my fingernails
are ripped out...

02:56.875 --> 02:58.244
‐Jesus.
‐Exactly.

02:58.278 --> 03:00.883
That is something that
a regular person can imagine.

03:00.917 --> 03:02.252
Okay.

03:02.286 --> 03:03.823
Have you ever
tied a knot before?

03:08.064 --> 03:10.737
You will not be able
to get out of this.

03:10.770 --> 03:12.774
It's important that
you believe that.

03:12.807 --> 03:14.811
‐Hey, buddy. Yeah.

03:30.175 --> 03:31.812
‐Shit!

05:12.212 --> 05:15.218
‐Yorick?

05:15.252 --> 05:18.324
‐Hey. Yorick.

05:21.698 --> 05:23.936
Shh. It's okay, it's okay, Amp.

05:23.969 --> 05:25.673
He's alive.

05:28.913 --> 05:31.184
You're okay.

05:33.354 --> 05:35.158
355?

05:47.149 --> 05:48.853
Okay.

06:03.381 --> 06:05.452
355?

06:12.199 --> 06:17.075
Help! Help!

06:25.526 --> 06:27.730
Shit.

06:27.764 --> 06:29.333
Come on, Yorick.

06:29.366 --> 06:31.872
Come on. Come on. Come on.

06:31.905 --> 06:34.076
Come on.

06:40.823 --> 06:43.094
CIA, maybe;
could be foreign‐made;

06:43.127 --> 06:46.200
certainly not military‐issue.

06:46.234 --> 06:48.004
How long were you unconscious?

06:48.037 --> 06:49.139
Couple of hours.

06:49.173 --> 06:50.408
Woke up,
and our boots were gone.

06:50.442 --> 06:53.047
We tracked her from
Boston. The soldiers at Harvard

06:53.081 --> 06:54.918
said that she was
looking for a scientist.

06:54.951 --> 06:56.254
Dr. Allison Mann.

06:56.287 --> 06:58.024
Some kind of geneticist.

06:58.057 --> 06:59.928
‐You get a visual on Dr. Mann?
‐No.

06:59.961 --> 07:02.065
Uh, but...

07:02.099 --> 07:03.969
What?

07:05.305 --> 07:07.142
I didn't see the doctor,

07:07.175 --> 07:09.079
but the third person
in the church,

07:09.113 --> 07:11.217
it was a man. I saw him.

07:11.250 --> 07:13.421
‐A man?
‐Burgin was protecting him.

07:13.454 --> 07:15.191
‐How close were you?
‐Close enough.

07:15.225 --> 07:17.029
‐Ten feet, maybe less?
‐Well, let's

07:17.062 --> 07:19.133
all acknowledge
there are men out there.

07:19.166 --> 07:21.337
‐I don't think
he was transgender, ma'am.
‐You're telling me you can

07:21.370 --> 07:22.472
verify someone's chromosomes
from ten feet?

07:22.507 --> 07:25.278
No, but why else

07:25.312 --> 07:27.416
would Agent Burgin be
looking for a geneticist?

07:27.449 --> 07:29.253
If she's protecting an asset...

07:29.286 --> 07:31.357
‐A survivor.
‐Oh, here we go.

07:31.390 --> 07:34.396
Well, it would explain
a few things, wouldn't it?

07:34.430 --> 07:37.035
Did you see him? This survivor?

07:37.069 --> 07:39.206
I'm asking them.

07:39.239 --> 07:41.444
‐No, ma'am.
‐No.

07:42.914 --> 07:45.586
With all due respect, Captain,
you were tranquilized.

07:45.619 --> 07:47.924
Your memory isn't
exactly reliable.

07:49.159 --> 07:50.896
I know what I saw.

07:51.932 --> 07:53.502
Did you notice
the crowds outside?

07:53.535 --> 07:55.840
‐Yes, ma'am.
‐The White House is gone.

07:55.873 --> 07:58.879
Those people doused one
of our guards with gasoline,

07:58.912 --> 08:00.583
tried to light her on fire.

08:00.616 --> 08:03.488
They will jump at anything that
has a whiff of conspiracy.

08:03.522 --> 08:05.458
So you'd better be sure.

08:05.492 --> 08:07.997
I'm sure as I can be.

08:08.031 --> 08:11.070
Caucasian, brown hair,
about six feet tall.

08:11.103 --> 08:13.107
Tell them the rest.

08:13.141 --> 08:15.445
"The rest"?

08:15.478 --> 08:17.950
There was an animal with him,
on his shoulder.

08:17.984 --> 08:19.453
‐Oh.
‐I know how it sounds.

08:19.486 --> 08:21.057
I think we're done here, Peggy.

08:21.090 --> 08:24.163
‐What kind of animal?
‐It matters?

08:24.196 --> 08:25.198
A monkey, ma'am.

08:25.231 --> 08:26.835
Thank you, Captain.

08:29.507 --> 08:31.177
Fuck.

08:32.279 --> 08:33.982
Get them reassigned.

08:34.016 --> 08:36.120
I don't want them spreading
that story in this building.

08:36.153 --> 08:37.857
‐Yes, ma'am.
‐Make it happen today.

08:40.095 --> 08:42.099
We're ready for you now,
Madam President.

08:42.132 --> 08:44.303
Thank you, Abby, lead the way.

08:53.488 --> 08:55.458
Do I look okay?
I mean, not okay,

08:55.492 --> 08:58.297
‐just not too polished.
‐You've threaded
the needle perfectly.

08:58.331 --> 09:00.936
All right. Let's do this.

09:00.970 --> 09:02.573
‐WOMAN Testing.

09:02.607 --> 09:04.043
Testing, one, two, three.

09:04.076 --> 09:05.880
Testing.
Testing, one, two, three.

09:05.913 --> 09:07.884
They're gonna throw her

09:07.917 --> 09:11.057
on a‐‐ on a Humvee like she's
Abraham fricking Lincoln

09:11.090 --> 09:12.627
on a whistle‐stop tour?

09:12.660 --> 09:16.467
Moths.

09:16.500 --> 09:18.071
HAWKEYE No,
I'd rather be a live chicken.

09:18.104 --> 09:20.075
In the Pentagon.

09:20.108 --> 09:21.444
This is my favorite sweater.

09:21.477 --> 09:23.314
Leave Jennifer Brown alone,
okay?

09:23.347 --> 09:25.686
‐She's a decent human being.

09:25.719 --> 09:26.822
She called Daddy a sexist
to score

09:26.855 --> 09:29.126
‐some cheap political points.

09:29.159 --> 09:31.030
And now she's sitting
in his chair...

09:31.063 --> 09:33.067
HAWKEYE I was hoping
I'd make it to Thursday.

09:33.101 --> 09:35.371
...while you sit here
watching your 47th episode

09:35.405 --> 09:38.044
‐of MASH.

09:38.077 --> 09:40.583
Well, I'm not the queen
of England, Kimberly.

09:40.616 --> 09:42.653
No one cares what I have to say.

09:42.687 --> 09:45.191
That's because you haven't
said anything. I mean,

09:45.225 --> 09:47.329
‐at least Regina is out there...

09:47.362 --> 09:48.565
Regina's a nutjob.

09:48.599 --> 09:50.636
And your father would be
the first to say so.

09:50.669 --> 09:52.239
Daddy chose her.

09:52.272 --> 09:55.078
She was loyal to him,
which means she's loyal to us.

09:55.111 --> 09:57.917
‐These are all ruined.

10:01.357 --> 10:03.494
A‐Are you gonna use
all those pillows?

10:03.529 --> 10:05.398
You're not giving that girl
my pillows.

10:05.432 --> 10:08.539
Her name is Christine
and she's pregnant.

10:09.974 --> 10:11.444
She needs friends.

10:15.185 --> 10:17.189
‐Oh...

10:17.222 --> 10:20.161
‐Your dad loved this one.
‐You've got a good sense
of humor,

10:20.195 --> 10:21.497
‐but a lousy sense of timing.
‐Come here.

10:21.531 --> 10:22.600
Fire that weapon.

10:22.633 --> 10:24.102
‐Fire it?

10:24.136 --> 10:25.539
I don't even like looking at it.

10:25.573 --> 10:27.977
Okay, you know what?
That's it. Get up.

10:29.012 --> 10:31.283
Get up! We're all suffering.

10:31.317 --> 10:34.089
Suffering? Really?

10:34.122 --> 10:35.960
Well, if you shed
even half a tear,

10:35.993 --> 10:37.630
your boys would
have to split it.

10:37.663 --> 10:40.068
POTTER
Fire the gun, Hawkeye.

10:40.101 --> 10:42.205
Look, Colonel...

10:42.239 --> 10:44.109
I'm gonna see them again.

10:44.143 --> 10:47.015
Yeah.
When you're dead.

10:47.048 --> 10:49.219
But I will not
inflict their wounds.

10:49.253 --> 10:51.123
You can't just sit there.

11:28.765 --> 11:31.337
Amp?

11:36.113 --> 11:37.516
Amp?

12:06.173 --> 12:08.044
Amp?

12:30.321 --> 12:31.758
Oh, God, don't touch it.

12:31.791 --> 12:35.098
She's bleeding.
Look at her little paw.

12:35.131 --> 12:37.102
Yeah, did you
hear about the woman

12:37.135 --> 12:39.807
who got her face ripped off
by a monkey in Connecticut?

12:39.841 --> 12:42.312
What the hell was a monkey
doing in Connecticut, huh?

12:43.849 --> 12:45.552
You're awake.

12:48.892 --> 12:50.261
Uh...

13:00.481 --> 13:02.452
Start with why you're here.

13:02.485 --> 13:04.891
Well, I don't know
where "here" is.

13:04.924 --> 13:08.264
Um, the people I was
in the truck with...

13:08.297 --> 13:09.867
You don't have to
worry about them.

13:09.901 --> 13:13.608
Okay. Um, listen, can I,
can I take him out of there?

13:13.642 --> 13:15.779
‐He's scared.
‐He?

13:16.948 --> 13:19.419
Uh, yeah.

13:19.453 --> 13:22.860
Yes. He's a...

13:22.893 --> 13:25.699
Yeah, I don't know how.
Um... Hey, hey.

13:25.733 --> 13:28.337
Hey, it's okay, buddy.

13:28.371 --> 13:30.576
‐So, where are my friends?
‐Friends?

13:30.609 --> 13:32.713
‐W‐What friends?
‐So you've got a Y chromosome?

13:32.747 --> 13:34.884
‐How did you survive?

13:34.917 --> 13:37.188
I, uh...

13:37.222 --> 13:40.428
I have no idea. I don't‐‐
uh, maybe I'm cursed.

13:42.298 --> 13:44.169
I'm not cursed
with a Y chromosome,

13:44.202 --> 13:46.407
but I'm cursed in
plenty of other ways.

13:46.440 --> 13:48.679
Thank you. Holy shit.

13:48.712 --> 13:50.783
Toast.

13:50.816 --> 13:52.853
This...

13:52.887 --> 13:54.489
Um...

13:54.524 --> 13:56.628
You guys have electricity.

13:56.661 --> 13:59.199
‐How?
‐Teamwork.

13:59.232 --> 14:01.504
‐Come on, buddy.
‐I imagine that you

14:01.538 --> 14:03.474
attract quite a bit
of attention.

14:03.508 --> 14:06.480
You know, more than before,
that's for sure.

14:06.514 --> 14:08.719
Oh, God.

14:08.752 --> 14:10.556
Mmm.

14:10.589 --> 14:12.660
Are there other survivors?

14:12.693 --> 14:15.331
Well, God, I hope so.

14:20.609 --> 14:22.913
Um...

14:22.947 --> 14:27.623
So, uh, yeah, my friends?
The other people in the truck?

14:27.656 --> 14:28.892
Thought you said
his hands were tied.

14:28.925 --> 14:30.395
They were.

14:30.428 --> 14:32.900
‐Your friends tied you up?
‐Oh, no. No, no.

14:32.933 --> 14:35.973
I was, um...
I was doing a trick.

14:36.006 --> 14:38.444
‐A trick?
‐Yeah, I'm an escape artist.

14:38.477 --> 14:41.718
‐Is that a joke?
‐Jokes are funny.

14:42.920 --> 14:44.924
We thought you were
being held captive.

14:44.957 --> 14:46.761
Uh, no.

14:46.795 --> 14:48.431
No.

14:52.338 --> 14:54.209
W‐Where are they?
Are they okay?

15:14.349 --> 15:16.320
Ah...

16:43.728 --> 16:45.966
We need help in here!

16:50.007 --> 16:51.711
Hello?

16:53.849 --> 16:56.353
‐Hey!
‐Shit.

16:56.386 --> 16:58.992
We need help in here!

17:00.428 --> 17:03.467
Anybody! Come on!

17:05.806 --> 17:07.877
Hey!

17:07.910 --> 17:10.114
We need help in here!

17:11.818 --> 17:13.722
Hello?! Come on!

17:13.755 --> 17:15.726
Where are we?

17:16.761 --> 17:19.567
‐What happened?
‐You crashed the truck.

17:19.600 --> 17:22.873
People came out of the woods,
brought us here.

17:24.109 --> 17:25.746
Where's Yorick?

17:25.779 --> 17:27.917
They took him off somewhere.

17:27.950 --> 17:29.820
He was unconscious.

17:34.797 --> 17:36.534
Shit.

17:40.107 --> 17:41.476
‐Hey, hey, hey, hey. Sit.
‐No.

17:41.511 --> 17:43.047
Sit. Sit down.

17:43.080 --> 17:45.586
Tell me everything
you can remember.

17:45.619 --> 17:47.823
How many were there?

17:47.856 --> 17:49.694
How'd they get in here?

17:50.996 --> 17:53.000
Four, I think.

17:53.033 --> 17:54.704
Or five.

17:54.737 --> 17:57.075
Two of them took Yorick,
the others brought us here.

17:57.108 --> 17:58.645
Were they armed?

17:58.678 --> 18:00.716
Yeah.

18:00.749 --> 18:03.521
Shotguns? Pistols?
Semiautos, what?

18:03.555 --> 18:05.826
I don't know.
Little guns. Big guns.

18:05.859 --> 18:07.529
They all had guns.

18:12.105 --> 18:15.011
‐Did you catch any names?
‐Uh...

18:15.044 --> 18:18.618
‐How'd they communicate?
‐It happened pretty fast.

18:19.687 --> 18:20.756
What are you doing?

18:20.789 --> 18:22.626
‐What's the plan?
‐I don't know,

18:22.660 --> 18:24.429
last time I told you the plan,

18:24.462 --> 18:26.834
you fucked off
in the middle of the night

18:26.868 --> 18:28.437
with humanity's last hope.

18:28.470 --> 18:31.511
You know,
I'm a little bit smart.

18:31.544 --> 18:34.449
‐I might be able to contribute.
‐No, no.

18:34.482 --> 18:38.525
I'll get us out of here,
we'll go find Yorick. Just‐‐

18:38.558 --> 18:40.161
shit‐‐ stop talking.

18:40.194 --> 18:43.868
No, no, you're right.
You got this.

18:43.902 --> 18:46.741
Long as there aren't any trees
between here and California,

18:46.774 --> 18:48.477
we should be good.

18:51.951 --> 18:54.155
The buses are available now

18:54.189 --> 18:56.861
to take you to
the Safe Settlement Zone

18:56.894 --> 18:58.698
just outside the city.

18:58.732 --> 19:02.973
There's hot food, showers,
medical attention.

19:03.007 --> 19:05.979
Of course, you have
every right to stay,

19:06.013 --> 19:09.119
protest, peaceably assemble.

19:09.152 --> 19:11.023
But we want you to be safe.

19:11.056 --> 19:15.097
Take advantage of access
to proper shelter and care.

19:15.131 --> 19:20.642
Though we do not yet know
what caused this...

19:20.676 --> 19:22.613
Sorry.

19:24.249 --> 19:27.255
...this terrible event,

19:27.288 --> 19:32.231
we are making enormous strides
every day...

19:34.169 --> 19:35.906
‐Ma'am?
‐Where are you going?
‐Ma'am?

19:35.939 --> 19:37.241
‐It's okay.
‐Please.
‐Madam President.

19:37.275 --> 19:40.147
‐There's somebody out there.
‐Ma'am, it's not safe.

19:43.020 --> 19:45.057
It's okay. It's okay.

19:45.091 --> 19:48.030
Let her through!
Let her through!

19:48.063 --> 19:49.667
It's okay.

19:51.971 --> 19:53.107
Beth.

19:57.348 --> 19:59.052
Thank you.

20:02.559 --> 20:06.934
You are a sight for sore eyes.

20:06.968 --> 20:08.137
Where's Hero?

20:09.305 --> 20:11.744
Well, we couldn't find her.

20:11.778 --> 20:13.982
‐Oh, I'm sorry.
‐Come. Sit.

20:14.015 --> 20:17.288
What about you?
Your family? Your mom?

20:18.658 --> 20:19.760
Oh...

20:21.764 --> 20:24.102
Yeah. A few weeks after.

20:24.135 --> 20:26.607
The doctors didn't
have time for her.

20:26.641 --> 20:28.711
Well, did you make it?
Were you with her?

20:28.745 --> 20:33.755
No. Uh, the roads were...
I didn't make it.

20:33.788 --> 20:35.659
Oh.

20:35.692 --> 20:37.663
I'm so sorry. If I...

20:37.696 --> 20:39.600
if I could have helped, I‐I...

20:39.633 --> 20:40.969
I could have made a call, or...

20:41.002 --> 20:43.040
I know. Thank you.

20:45.912 --> 20:48.852
Wow. Where were you when...

20:48.885 --> 20:51.223
I was on my bike.

20:51.256 --> 20:53.360
Um, I woke up in triage.

20:53.393 --> 20:55.064
They told me what happened.

20:55.097 --> 20:57.368
‐Yeah.
‐It didn't feel real.

20:57.401 --> 20:59.673
But I could walk so...

21:00.942 --> 21:04.617
I made it back to our street,
but I couldn't go in.

21:04.650 --> 21:07.790
I couldn't see him like that.

21:12.933 --> 21:14.102
You must be very hungry.

21:14.135 --> 21:16.741
I'll have Christine
bring up some food, okay?

21:19.078 --> 21:21.216
I can't believe
you're the president.

21:21.249 --> 21:25.725
Yeah.
Yeah, don't get me started.

21:25.759 --> 21:26.994
It's a dead end.

21:27.028 --> 21:29.265
There's no proof that
Burgin killed the pilots,

21:29.299 --> 21:31.871
much less that it was
ordered by the president.

21:31.904 --> 21:34.142
That doesn't mean
it didn't happen.

21:34.175 --> 21:37.683
‐Kimber, refill?
‐What did the soldiers say?

21:37.716 --> 21:39.419
‐Was there anyone with her?
‐Two others.

21:39.452 --> 21:41.691
‐Kimberly.
‐Hero?

21:41.724 --> 21:43.093
They were hit
with tranquilizers.

21:43.127 --> 21:45.699
Their stories were
all over the place.

21:45.732 --> 21:47.936
But no, I mean,
it didn't sound like it.

21:47.970 --> 21:49.640
Hero is, um, kind of short,

21:49.673 --> 21:52.746
doesn't really brush her hair.
She looks like a drug addict.

21:52.779 --> 21:55.184
‐That's not the
description they gave.
‐What was the description?

21:55.217 --> 21:57.121
‐Give it a rest, Kimber.
‐I'm telling you,
it's a dead end.

21:57.155 --> 21:59.092
‐Can you just tell me?
‐REGINA Okay.

21:59.125 --> 22:02.198
Uh, six feet tall with a monkey
on his shoulder. You happy?

22:09.112 --> 22:11.349
