May he walk the earth in steps
of purpose and grace.

39:30.093 --> 39:31.228
Amen.

39:43.052 --> 39:45.056
Was I in there for too long?

39:45.089 --> 39:46.893
I haven't had
a real shower in...

39:46.927 --> 39:48.797
Of course not.
I'll have Christine

39:48.830 --> 39:51.068
bring up some clean clothes.

39:51.101 --> 39:54.207
The first lady...

39:54.241 --> 39:55.844
Yeah?

39:55.878 --> 39:57.013
She's been through an awful lot.

39:57.047 --> 40:00.086
Kimberly's three boys were
with her that morning and...

40:00.119 --> 40:03.459
they were all in bed together
watching a movie, so...

40:03.492 --> 40:06.031
I thought I'd sleep out here.

40:06.065 --> 40:08.804
‐Give you the bed.
‐Oh.

40:08.837 --> 40:10.440
No. I can't stay.

40:10.473 --> 40:12.110
Oh, I thought...

40:12.143 --> 40:12.979
I just wanted to see you,

40:13.012 --> 40:16.452
and talk to somebody else
who loved him.

40:17.855 --> 40:20.460
Well, if you don't want to
sleep here, there's a dorm...

40:20.493 --> 40:21.930
No, you had to make rules.

40:21.963 --> 40:23.232
You can't let everybody in.

40:23.266 --> 40:25.403
And I'm not actually your...

40:25.436 --> 40:27.440
Well, you may as well be.

40:29.177 --> 40:31.382
I just wanted you to know
that I loved him.

40:35.858 --> 40:38.229
‐Where will you go?
‐Oh, um,

40:38.262 --> 40:39.933
I'm staying with friends.

40:39.966 --> 40:42.805
Sydney. You remember her?

40:42.838 --> 40:44.274
I don't know actually
if you ever met her,

40:44.308 --> 40:47.815
but her mom has a house
on Lake Anna,

40:47.848 --> 40:51.088
and they've got well water,
so...

40:51.121 --> 40:54.963
it's pretty nice,
all things considered.

40:56.866 --> 41:01.241
You know, your jacket lining
is thinning.

41:01.275 --> 41:03.379
I thought you might
like this one.

41:03.412 --> 41:05.216
It's much warmer.

41:06.553 --> 41:09.959
‐Oh, no, I can't take that.
‐I hardly wear it. It's yours.

41:09.993 --> 41:12.330
I can't wear this out there.

41:16.606 --> 41:19.812
Oh. Of course.

41:24.021 --> 41:28.563
Well, if you ever need anything,
you know where to find me and...

41:28.597 --> 41:31.536
‐I'm not going anywhere.
‐Thanks.

41:31.569 --> 41:33.105
Mm.

41:48.302 --> 41:51.342
There you go. Nice and easy.

41:51.375 --> 41:53.412
‐You want this up?
Up a little bit?
‐Yeah.

41:53.446 --> 41:56.285
Here. Okay, just one second.

41:56.318 --> 41:58.890
‐You got it.

41:58.924 --> 42:00.293
‐Is that okay?
‐Uh‐huh.

42:00.326 --> 42:01.563
Okay.

42:01.596 --> 42:04.334
Hey. Do me a favor.

42:06.305 --> 42:09.444
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

42:09.478 --> 42:12.417
Keep your mouth shut.

42:14.555 --> 42:16.559
Don't trust anybody.

42:17.661 --> 42:19.431
Okay.

42:19.464 --> 42:22.237
Especially that girl.

42:22.270 --> 42:24.575
‐What girl?
‐You know what girl.

42:24.609 --> 42:28.115
Just... just rest, okay?

42:28.149 --> 42:30.854
You won't have to do this again.

42:35.463 --> 42:38.302
You won't have to take care
of me like this again,

42:38.335 --> 42:40.239
‐I promise.
‐Hey.

42:41.475 --> 42:43.446
It's okay.

42:45.450 --> 42:46.553
I know.

43:11.736 --> 43:15.376
‐Yeah, so, I was hoping I could
get some more of that stuff.
‐Yeah, yeah, cool.

43:15.409 --> 43:17.515
You coming?

43:17.548 --> 43:20.386
Oh, my God, she's gotten
so good at that.

43:20.419 --> 43:23.225
‐Right? I know.
‐Yeah, she's been
practicing forever.

43:23.259 --> 43:25.096
Although, you know what,

43:25.129 --> 43:27.066
I think, I think
I'm gonna join her...

43:27.100 --> 43:29.337
Oh, no! Oh, my God...

44:17.300 --> 44:19.639
‐Hey.
‐Hi.

44:19.672 --> 44:21.041
Grab some grub.

44:21.074 --> 44:23.212
‐Uh, just here?
‐Mm‐hmm.

44:37.273 --> 44:40.046
‐Thank you. Mm‐hmm.
‐Hey.

44:40.079 --> 44:42.450
‐Oh, hey. Hi.
‐Hey.

44:42.483 --> 44:43.720
Not bad, right?

44:43.753 --> 44:46.158
‐Yeah. I mean...

44:49.231 --> 44:52.303
So, um, you really
an escape artist?

44:52.337 --> 44:54.174
Mm‐hmm. Yeah.

44:55.376 --> 44:58.282
Couldn't get out of that cell.

44:58.315 --> 45:01.288
I think with enough time,
maybe, I, um...

45:02.658 --> 45:05.731
But no, no, not really.
That's a fricking prison cell.

45:05.764 --> 45:07.433
‐Um...

45:07.467 --> 45:10.707
‐Aw, it's okay.
‐No, it's, uh...

45:10.741 --> 45:12.578
Yeah, it's like, um,

45:12.611 --> 45:15.617
it's like Houdini stuff‐‐
so handcuffs and straitjackets

45:15.651 --> 45:17.621
‐and water tanks...
‐Oh, is there money in that?

45:17.655 --> 45:19.491
Uh, not so far.

45:21.461 --> 45:24.100
What's with the monkey?

45:24.134 --> 45:26.806
He's my best friend.

45:27.808 --> 45:30.747
This is ama‐‐ Who‐who made this?

45:30.781 --> 45:33.485
Uh, Janis made it.
She's a good cook.

45:35.356 --> 45:38.462
She's good at a lot of things,
actually.

45:38.495 --> 45:40.499
Mm.

45:46.813 --> 45:51.221
‐How did she end up, uh...
‐In prison?

46:00.540 --> 46:02.711
She stabbed two people to death.

46:03.713 --> 46:07.353
In 1978.
She was 21, strung out.

46:07.387 --> 46:09.692
Guys she did it with
got executed in the '90s.

46:09.725 --> 46:11.261
Holy shit.

46:11.295 --> 46:15.269
She's harmless.
She reads Angela Davis and shit.

46:15.303 --> 46:17.373
Don't worry about Janis.

46:20.179 --> 46:22.551
Um...

46:22.584 --> 46:24.555
Thanks for letting us stay.

46:24.588 --> 46:27.828
Well, we voted, so...

46:27.861 --> 46:31.501
‐How was our margin of victory?
‐Not great.

46:31.536 --> 46:33.807
Okay. Good to know.

46:33.840 --> 46:36.579
That's, uh‐‐ we'll, um...

46:36.612 --> 46:39.284
I will stay out of the way.

46:47.735 --> 46:49.772
Should've let 'em bleed out
on the side of the road.

46:49.805 --> 46:51.375
Very charitable, Dom.

46:51.408 --> 46:53.412
You're a real fucking
ray of sunshine.

46:53.445 --> 46:55.383
Somebody's chasing them.

46:55.416 --> 46:57.655
And if they are,
they're looking for him.

46:57.688 --> 46:59.592
Yeah? Think they might
have a few questions

46:59.625 --> 47:01.696
when they get here?
"What happened to the guards?

47:01.729 --> 47:03.533
Where are all the people
that used to live here?"

47:05.336 --> 47:06.673
We tell them the truth.

47:06.706 --> 47:09.477
Yeah? When's the fucking truth
worked out for you?

47:09.512 --> 47:11.749
Shit, Janis, now you sound
fucking stupid.

47:13.620 --> 47:15.791
What did you say to me,
little girl?

47:17.628 --> 47:19.464
That right there?

47:19.497 --> 47:22.838
That's gonna get us all killed.
Tell her not to get attached.

47:28.717 --> 47:30.286
What's that?

47:30.319 --> 47:34.361
Uh, lights out at00.
Gotta preserve what we have.

47:34.394 --> 47:35.697
Mm.

48:37.588 --> 48:40.560
Mama? I got peaches.

48:42.330 --> 48:44.501
I traded Elaine for them.

48:44.535 --> 48:47.440
She's got, like, a whole
supermarket down there.

48:47.473 --> 48:50.947
It's crazy. I don't know where
she gets the hookup from.

48:50.981 --> 48:53.520
It's pretty great.
Now all we need is

48:53.553 --> 48:59.297
some butter and I think
we are halfway to a cobbler.

48:59.330 --> 49:02.571
I think we deserve
something sweet, don't you?

49:02.604 --> 49:06.278
Mama?

49:24.748 --> 49:26.652
Mom?

49:38.475 --> 49:42.350
No!

49:42.383 --> 49:46.091
No!

49:46.124 --> 49:48.997
Mom!

50:17.688 --> 50:20.527
I wasn't sure if you'd be here.

50:20.560 --> 50:21.929
I said I would be.

50:21.963 --> 50:25.670
So, you saw her?
They let you in?

50:25.704 --> 50:27.741
Yeah.

50:27.774 --> 50:30.614
What's it like in there?

50:30.647 --> 50:34.655
Warm water, food, power.

50:34.688 --> 50:37.393
It's a time machine.

50:37.426 --> 50:40.499
But it could all fall apart.

50:40.534 --> 50:42.470
And it wouldn't take much.

50:47.781 --> 50:49.652
‐Let's go!

50:49.685 --> 50:52.724
Everyone's waiting.
